{"lemma":"حَياةُ","slug":"حَياةُ","root":"ح.#.#","root_slug":"ح-_-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-_-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حَياة","root":"حيي","pos":"N","occurrence_count":76},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n9663","n9675"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَيِيَ (ḥayiya) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"life","examples":[{"text":"هٰذَا كِتَابٌ جَدِيدٌ عَنْ حَيَاةِ النِّسَاءِ الْعَرَبِيَّاتِ.","english":"This is a new book about the life of Arab women."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Cognate with Biblical Hebrew חַיִּים (ḥayyím, “life”), Aramaic חֲיֶא (ḥăyyē, “life”) and Classical Syriac ܚܝܐ (ḥayyē, “life”)."},"ipa":["/ħa.jaːh/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n9663","headword_ar":"حيّاهُ","root":"HY: or HY and Hyw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHiy~apN","text_ar":"تَحِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb, K,) in its primary sense,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHyAhu","text_ar":"احياهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hay~aAka A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"حَيَّاكَ ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God preserve thee alive; prolong thy life;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"make thee to continue in life;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboqaAka","text_ar":"اَبْقَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Fr, Selemeh Ibn- 'Ásim, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHyAk","text_ar":"احياك","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Selemeh Ibn-'Ásim, TA;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eam~araka","text_ar":"عَمَّرَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Aboo-'Othmán El-Mázinee, Mgh, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may God save thee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"make thee to be free from evil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"harm,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may God make thee to have dominion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may God honour thee, and benefit thee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham. p. 489.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hay~aAka A@ll~`hu wabay~aAka","text_ar":"حَيَّاكَ ا@للّٰهُ وَبَيَّاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[explained in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bY","text_ar":"بى"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hay~aA A@ll~`hu wajohaka","text_ar":"حَيَّا ا@للّٰهُ وَجْهَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God preserve thy face:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHay~FA","text_ar":"مُحَيًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Ham p. 23.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He said to him"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hay~aAka A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"حَيَّاكَ ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", explained above: (Mgh:) originally,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he prayed for his life:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and then,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he prayed for him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"absolutely: (Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he saluted him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hy~Ahu taHiy~apa","text_ar":"حيّاهُ تَحِيَّةَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almuw^omini","text_ar":"المُوْمِنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Lh, TA:) as used in the language of the law,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he said to him,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salaAmN Ealayoka","text_ar":"سَلَامٌ عَلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) ―         -b3-  [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHiy~apN","text_ar":"تَحِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below.]       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hy~A Alxamosiyna","text_ar":"حيّا الخَمْسِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the CK (erroneously)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxamosiyna","text_ar":"الخَمْسِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~a","text_ar":"حَىَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He approached"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the age of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fifty."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K, TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hay~ayatu","text_ar":"حَيَّيَتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaA='F HasanpF","text_ar":"حَا=ءً حَسَنةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasanFA","text_ar":"حَسَنًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I wrote a beautiful"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"H","text_ar":"ح"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bAb AlAlf All~ynp","text_ar":"باب الالف اللّينة"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["Mgh","Msb","K","S","Fr","TA","Lh"]},{"entry_id":"n9675","headword_ar":"حَيَاةٌ","root":"HY: or HY and Hyw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hay`wp","text_ar":"حَيٰوة","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (as in different copies of the K, in the latter manner in copies of the S,) written with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Kur, to show that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"follows"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the pl. ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayawaAtN","text_ar":"حَيَوَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalawaAtN","text_ar":"صَلَوَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], or because the sound of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is inclined towards that of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":", (ISd, TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayawopN","text_ar":"حَيَوْةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with sukoon to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) which is substituted for the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayaApN","text_ar":"حَيَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as is done by the people of El-Yemen in the case of every"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"that is changed from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalaApN","text_ar":"صَلَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zakaApN","text_ar":"زَكَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", though the final radical letter of the verb of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayaApN","text_ar":"حَيَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayiYa","text_ar":"حَيِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the first of the senses explained in this art.; (IB, Mgh, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Life; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawotN","text_ar":"مَوْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayawaAnN","text_ar":"حَيَوَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiY~N","text_ar":"حِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or this last is asserted to be a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hay`wpN","text_ar":"حَيٰوةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) and as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHoyFA","text_ar":"مَحْيًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, * Har pp. 25 and 350,) of which the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHaAYK","text_ar":"مَحَاىٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayaApN","text_ar":"حَيَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"faculty of growth, as in an animal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a plant:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"faculty of sensation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and (assumed tropical:)  the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"faculty of intellect:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"freedom from grief"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sorrow:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"everlasting life in the world to come;"},{"kind":"text","text":"to which one attains by that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HyAp","text_ar":"حياة"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is intelligence and knowledge: and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HyAp","text_ar":"حياة"},{"kind":"text","text":"that is an attribute of God. (Er-Rághib.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA layotaniY","text_ar":"يَا لَيْتَنِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qad~amotu liHayaAtiY","text_ar":"قَدَّمْتُ لِحَيَاتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [lxxxix. 25], means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O, would that I had prepared,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"laid up in store,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for my everlasting state of existence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA_in~a Ald~aAra AlA=xirapa lahiYa AlHayawaAnu","text_ar":"فَاـِنَّ الدَّارَ الا=خِرَةَ لَهِىَ الحَيَوَانُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [xxix. 64], means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And verily the last abode is"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the abode of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"everlasting life:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHywAn","text_ar":"الحيوان"},{"kind":"text","text":"here means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the life that will not be followed by death:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much life;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawataAnN","text_ar":"مَوَتَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies much death: (Msb:) and it is also the name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain fountain in Paradise,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the water of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which touches nothing but it lives, by permission of God."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHay`wpu AlT~ay~ibapu","text_ar":"الحَيٰوةُ الطَّيِّبَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to I'Ab, explaining xvi. 99 of the Kur, (TA,) means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lawful means of subsistence"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the present world:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Paradise."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) ―         -b2-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Advantage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"profit;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cause,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"means, thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"whence the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa lifulaAnK","text_ar":"لَيْسَ لِفُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayaApN","text_ar":"حَيَاةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is not, in such a one, profit, nor good:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so it is said to mean in the Kur [ii. 175],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walakumo fiY AlqiSaASi Hay`wpN","text_ar":"وَلَكُمْ فِى القِصَاصِ حَيٰوةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And there is to you, in retaliation, an advantage"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) or this means that the knowledge of the law of retaliation restrains from slaughter, and so is a cause of life to two persons; and because they used to slay one who was not the slayer, retaliation upon the slayer is a cause of saving the lives of the rest: or the meaning is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"life in the world to come;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for when the slayer has suffered retaliation in the present world, he is not punished for his act in the world to come. (Bd.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayaApu Al$~amosi","text_ar":"حَيَاةُ الشَّمْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The remaining of the light and whiteness of the sun:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the remaining of its heat and power:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but the former of these two meanings is the more probable. (Mgh. [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~amosu Hay~apN","text_ar":"الشَّمْسُ حَيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~N","text_ar":"حَىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])"}],"source_refs":["ISd","TA","K","S","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}